%N A395328 Bipartite dimension of the n-barbell graph.
%C A395328 The n-barbell graph is formed from two copies of K_n by joining a vertex of one copy to a vertex of the other copy by an edge.
%H A395328 Eric Weisstein's World of Mathematics, <a href="https://mathworld.wolfram.com/BarbellGraph.html">Barbell Graph</a>.
%H A395328 Eric Weisstein's World of Mathematics, <a href="https://mathworld.wolfram.com/BipartiteDimension.html">Bipartite Dimension</a>.
%F A395328 a(n) = 1 + ceiling(log_2(n - 1)) + ceiling(log_2(n)) for n >= 3.
%e A395328 a(3) = 4 since 1 + ceiling(log_2(2)) + ceiling(log_2(3)) = 4.
%t A395328 Table[1 + Ceiling[Log2[n - 1]] + Ceiling[Log2[n]], {n, 3, 20}]
%K A395328 nonn,easy
%O A395328 3,1
%A A395328 _Eric W. Weisstein_, Jun 29 2026
